text: Baths Island from upstream Baths Island from downstream Baths Island is an island in the River Thames in England on the reach above Romney Lock, between Eton Wick and Windsor, Berkshire. The island is unpopulated and contains public open space. It carries the central part of Windsor Railway Bridge across the river. ==See also== *Islands in the River Thames Category:Islands of Berkshire Category:Islands of the River Thames
